#### RichTextBox
Adding the property `IsTextSelectionEnabledProperty` for checking if the text selection is enabled/disabled. Some style triggers will be invoked if text selection is enabled/disabled.
##### Usage
```xaml
        <Style.Triggers>
            <Trigger Property="IsTextSelectionEnabled" Value="False">
                <Setter Property="Template" Value="{StaticResource DefaultUiTextBoxControlTemplate}" />
            </Trigger>
            <Trigger Property="IsTextSelectionEnabled" Value="True">
                <Setter Property="IsReadOnly" Value="True" />
                <Setter Property="Background" Value="Transparent" />
                <Setter Property="Padding" Value="0" />
                <Setter Property="BorderBrush" Value="Transparent" />
                <Setter Property="BorderThickness" Value="0" />
                <Setter Property="Template" Value="{StaticResource DefaultUiTextBoxTextSelectionEnabledControlTemplate}" />
            </Trigger>
        </Style.Triggers>
```
```diff
     public partial class RichTextBox : System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.TextBoxBase, System.Windows.Markup.IAddChild
     {
